250 g Ground Pork
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
2 unit(s) Peanut Butter
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
4 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
56 g Carrot, julienned
2 unit(s) Green Onion
9 g Moo Shu Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
1 unit(s) Lime
1 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
¼ tsp Pepper*

Before starting, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil (use same for 4 servings).
Wash and dry all produce.
Cut bok choy into 1/2-inch pieces. Rinse bok choy leaves to wash away any dirt.
Cut green onion whites into 1-inch pieces.
Thinly slice remaining green onion.
Juice half the lime into a small bowl, then cut remaining lime into wedges.
To the bowl with lime juice, add hoisin sauce, peanut butter, soy sauce, half the sesame oil and 2/3 cup (1 1/3 cups) warm water. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. Set aside.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then pork. Cook for 3-4 min, breaking up pork into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.
Add Moo Shu Spice Blend and green onion whites. Cook for 1-2 min, stirring often, until fragrant and onions are tender-crisp.
Transfer to a medium bowl, then cover to keep warm.

To the same pan, add remaining sesame oil, then bok choy and carrots. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp. Season with salt and pepper.

To the boiling water, add noodles. Cook for 1-3 min, stirring occasionally, until tender but still firm to the bite.
Strain and rinse noodles with warm water.
Return noodles to the pot, then add veggies and pork mixture.
Pour peanut sauce mixture into the pot. Cook for 1 min, stirring constantly, until well combined.
Remove from heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide peanut pork noodles between bowls.
Sprinkle with remaining green onions.
Squeeze over a lime wedge, if you like.